    <link>https://web.nvd.nist.gov/view/vuln/detail?vulnId=CVE-2020-13544</link>
    <description>An exploitable sign extension vulnerability exists in the TextMaker document parsing functionality of SoftMaker Office 2021&amp;acirc;&amp;euro;&amp;trade;s TextMaker application. A specially crafted document can cause the document parser to sign-extend a length used to terminate a loop, which can later result in the loop&amp;acirc;&amp;euro;&amp;trade;s index being used to write outside the bounds of a heap buffer during the reading of file data. An attacker can entice the victim to open a document to trigger this vulnerability.</description>
